# WHAT IT IS
#   KernelScript is "a domain-specific programming language for
#   eBPF-centric development" that unifies eBPF, userspace, and
#   kernelspace development in one codebase.  It generates
#   efficient C code for eBPF programs (xdp, tc, kprobe, uprobe,
#   tracepoint, struct_ops, cgroup, sk_msg, sk_skb, lsm, etc.),
#   coordinated userspace loaders, and kernel-module kfunc
#   exporters — all from a single `.ks` source file.  The driver
#   reads BTF (BPF Type Format) from `/sys/kernel/btf/vmlinux`
#   (or a configured path) to validate kfunc / struct-ops
#   signatures, generate `extern fn ...` declarations into a
#   companion `.kh` header, and emit Makefiles that wire the
#   resulting C files into a working build.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/main.ml top-level
#                       help string + per-subcommand
#                       `parse_init_args` / `parse_compile_args`
#                       — KernelScript uses a hand-rolled OCaml
#                       arg parser, not Cmdliner)
#   kernelscript <SUBCOMMAND> [options...]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     init <PROG_TYPE_OR_STRUCT_OPS> <PROJECT_NAME>
#                                    Initialize a new KernelScript
#                                    project
#       --btf-vmlinux-path <PATH>      Path to BTF vmlinux file
#                                      [default: /sys/kernel/btf/
#                                                vmlinux]
#       --kfuncs                       Extract available kfuncs
#                                      from BTF and generate
#                                      `.kh` header file
#
#     compile <INPUT_FILE>           Compile KernelScript source
#                                    to C code (eBPF + userspace
#                                    + optional kernel module)
#       -o, --output <DIR>             Output directory
#       -v, --verbose                  Verbose output
#       --no-makefile                  Don't generate Makefile
#       --test                         Compile in test mode
#                                      (only @test functions
#                                       become `main`)
#       --builtin-path <PATH>          Path to builtin .ks files
#       --btf-vmlinux-path <PATH>      Path to BTF vmlinux file
#                                      [default: /sys/kernel/btf/
#                                                vmlinux]
#
#   Standard auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#
#   Valid PROG_TYPE values:
#     xdp                            XDP packet processor
#     tc/<DIRECTION>                 TC classifier
#                                    (tc/ingress | tc/egress)
#     probe/<TARGET_FUNCTION>        K(re)probe / U(re)probe
#                                    (e.g. probe/sys_read,
#                                          probe/vfs_write,
#                                          probe/tcp_sendmsg)
#     tracepoint/<CATEGORY>/<EVENT>  Tracepoint
#                                    (e.g.
#                                    tracepoint/syscalls/
#                                    sys_enter_read,
#                                    tracepoint/sched/
#                                    sched_switch)
#     <struct_ops>                   struct_ops kernel hook
#                                    (tcp_congestion_ops |
#                                     sched_ext_ops | etc.)
